	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000955_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<!-- This file needs to be rechecked since it was mangled by word MH 2005-12-18 - checked CO 2006-01-26 --><!-- PB element? MH 2005-12-18 --><!--Hand 01 9 top left--><!--Hand 02 68011 superscript A top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St.</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">London 27 <choice><abbr>Jan<hi rend="sup">y</hi></abbr><expan>January</expan></choice>.</p><!--Hand 03 1857 under date-->
<lb/><p><hi rend="underline">Private</hi><!--this is written across top left-hand corner--></p>
<lb/><p>Sir</p>
<lb/><p>I have been 
<lb/>requested by <persName>Mr Prout</persName>
<lb/>to reply to a note you 
<lb/>sent to him respecting 
<lb/>my acceptance 
<lb/>of the Freedom of 
<lb/>the City of Edinburgh.</p>
<lb/><p>If I consult my 
<lb/>own inclinations 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_000955_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>I have not the the smallest 
<lb/>desire to <choice><sic>recieve</sic><corr>receive</corr></choice> any 
<lb/>civic honours. I 
<lb/>wish to finish my 
<lb/>present work with 
<lb/>all expedition and 
<lb/>hasten back to my 
<lb/>men who now 
<lb/>await the fullfillment 
<lb/>of my promise at 
<lb/><placeName>Tete</placeName>. The writing of 
<lb/>my work will occupy 
<lb/>me fully to the end of 
<lb/>April. I shall then <choice><abbr>D. V.</abbr><expan>Deo Volente, God Willing</expan></choice><!-- The coding of the abbr is correct but logically, I would not put two values into the expan attribute. Strictly speaking, it should be Deo Volente. However, it would be nice to also have a 'normalized' value of 'God Willing' as well. This is beyond the DTD at present, but can be addressed -->

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_000955_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>pay my last visit to 
<lb/>my good mother 
<lb/>in Hamilton. If that 
<lb/>time would be suitable 
<lb/>and you see that the 
<lb/>gentlemen still feel 
<lb/>inclined to confer the 
<lb/>honour I shall come 
<lb/>but hope no public 
<lb/>demonstration will 
<lb/>be made. Those public 
<lb/>meetings in London 
<lb/>have all been against 
<lb/>my judgement for 
<lb/>I cannot help fearing 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_000955_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/>if we protestants make 
<lb/>too much fuss opponents 
<lb/>who are now still 
<lb/>may be excited to spring 
<lb/>up against us. You 
<lb/>know the Portugese 
<lb/>are all Roman Catholics 
<lb/>If the gentlemen wish 
<lb/>to honour the cause 
<lb/>in which I am engaged 
<lb/>I must accede to 
<lb/>the honour and will 
<lb/>try to do it thankfully</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">Believe me Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">&amp;c</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">David Livingstone</p>
			
